        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Wintersleep"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Emerging from Halifax, Wintersleep has been quietly reshaping the contours of modern rock since their inception in 2001. Anchored by the evocative baritone of frontman Paul Murphy, alongside Loel Campbell’s hypnotic, propulsive drumming and Tim D’Eon’s shimmering guitar and piano work, the band conjures a sonic atmosphere that feels both vast and intimate. Their catalog, anchored by critically celebrated albums Untitled, Welcome to the Night Sky, Hello Hum, The Great Detachment and In the Land Of, occupies a distinct place in the Canadian indie rock canon, praised for its deft balance of haunting lyricism and cinematic grandeur. In 2025, Wintersleep brings with them a promise of immersive live performances—equal parts raw emotional catharsis and meticulously constructed sonic atmospheres. Longtime fans and new listeners alike will be drawn into the band’s enveloping soundscapes, where intimate confessions collide with epic swells of sound, capturing the delicate tension between vulnerability and grandeur that defines their music. [embed]https://youtu.be/47CuA9Bnh60[/embed]"
      }
    ],
