    "https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tCome From Away – Sep 18\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tLocation: Imperial Theatre\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tDate: Friday, September 18, 2026\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tShow Starts: 7:30 PM\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tTickets: $85 A / $80 B / $75 C\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\tSTYLE OF SHOW: Theatre/Musical\n\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tBuy Tickets\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tRead More\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tLocation: Imperial Theatre\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tDate: Friday, September 18, 2026\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tShow Starts: 7:30 PM\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tTickets: $85 A / $80 B / $75 C\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\tSTYLE OF SHOW: Theatre/Musical\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tBuy Tickets\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tRead More\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\t\tBook, Music and Lyrics by\nIRENE SANKOFF and DAVID HEIN\nDirected by Courtney and Tony LePage. Musical Direction by Michael Doherty.\nOriginal Broadway Production Produced by Junkyard Dog Productions.\nOrchestrations by August Eriksmoen. Arrangements by Ian Eisendrath.\n\nHomegrown Talent Takes Centre Stage – Starring Broadway’s Tony LePage and an All-New Brunswick Cast!\n\n\nBack by overwhelming demand, Come From Away is soaring across New Brunswick once again! Performed by an all–New Brunswick cast including Broadway’s own Tony LePage. This electrifying production is East Coast talent at its absolute best!\n\nInspired by true events, this smash-hit musical tells the remarkable story of kindness in the days following September 11, when strangers became family in the small town of Gander, Newfoundland. Bursting with humour, heart, and unforgettable music, Come From Away is fast-paced, joyful, and deeply moving.\n\nFunny, foot-stomping, and full of heart, this is the feel-good musical audiences can’t stop talking about. Proudly presented through a collaborative partnership between Saint John Theatre Company and Rogue Productions, Come From Away celebrates the power of community – onstage, offstage, and right here at home.\n\n\nBack by popular demand, Come From Away soars across New Brunswick! Performed by an all New Brunswick cast, including Broadway’s Tony LePage, this heartwarming, funny, and foot-stomping musical tells the true story of kindness in Gander, Newfoundland after 9/11. Don’t miss this joyful, unforgettable celebration of community! Presented by Saint John Theatre Company & Rogue Productions, Come From Away celebrates the power of community onstage, offstage, and at home.\n\nCOME FROM AWAY is presented through special arrangement with Music Theatre International (MTI). All authorized performance materials are also supplied by MTI. www.mtishows.com\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t"
      }
    ]
  },
